Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Add @water{300%ml}(cold, salted) and @chicken stock{1%sachet} to a #medium pot{} with a
lid.

Add the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, lower heat to medium and
cover.

Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat (still covered) and leave aside
until ready to serve.

Chop the @broccoli{1}(chopped into 1cm pieces) into 1cm pieces (or as small as you
can get it).

> TIP: Coarsely grate the broccoli if you prefer.

While the rice cooks, place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @chicken breast{260%g}(diced) and season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Fry until golden brown on the outside, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due
> to vacuum packing we use to keep it fresh. It will still be delicious once cooked!

Add the chopped broccoli to the pan along with another drizzle of oil (if necessary).

Fry until softened, stirring frequently, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @paprika{1%sachet} and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Transfer the broccoli and chicken to an appropriately-sized #oven dish{} and wipe
the pan clean.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with @?butter{2%tbsp} or oil.

> Double for 4p

When hot, stir in @flour{3%tbsp} and cook, stirring until it forms a paste,
~{1-2%minutes}—you've made a roux!

Gradually add @?milk{250%ml} or @?water{250%ml}.

> Double for 4p

Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from
the heat.

Add the @creme fraiche{125%g} along with half the @grated cheese{50%g} and stir until
melted. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Pour the bechamel sauce over the chicken and broccoli.

Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.

Bake in the oven until the cheese has melted and the sauce is bubbling,
~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Leave to rest for ~{5%minutes} before serving.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between plates.

Dish up a hearty helping of cheesy chicken and broccoli bake.